Fifty people representing 26 countries took the Oath of Allegiance this week
(Thursday) and became U.S. citizens in a special ceremony at the Newseum in
Washington, D.C. The ceremony was in held in honor of America's July 4
Independence Day holiday. VOA's Ana Ward spoke to some of the participants
about the significance of this day and their new life as American citizens. Jim
Bertel narrates.
 
 
 
 
 

